e taken away from their shoulders. }26.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  This is the purpose which the Lord has purposed upon the whole earth: and this the hand that is uplifted against all the nations. }27.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  For what the Holy God has purposed, who shall frustrate? and who shall turn back hi
s uplifted hand? }28.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  In the year in which king Achaz died this word came. }29.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Rejoice not, all ye Philistines, because the yoke of him that smote you is broken: for out of the seed of the serpent shall come forth the young asps, and their young shall come 
forth flying serpents, }30.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the poor shall be fed by him, and poor men shall rest in peace: but he shall destroy thy seed with hunger, and shall destroy thy remnant. }31.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Howl, ye gates of cities; let the cities be troubled and cry, [even] all the Philis
tines: for smoke is coming from the north, and there is no [possibility] of living. }32.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And what shall the kings of the nations answer? That the Lord has founded Sion, and by him the poor of the people shall be saved. }}
