\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s9\qj\rtlch\af5\afs20\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe1033\hich\f5\fs20\lang1033\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i\b0{\*\cs27\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\i\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i Reader:}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0  19.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A righteous son is born for life: but the persecution of the ungodly ends in death. }20.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Perverse ways are an abomination to the Lord: but all they that are blameless in their ways are acceptable to him. }21.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that unjustly strikes hands shall 
not be unpunished: but he that sows righteousness shall receive a faithful reward. }22.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  As an ornament in a swine's snout, so is beauty to an ill-minded woman. }23.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  All the desire of the righteous is good: but the hope of the ungodly shall perish. }24.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  There 
are some who scatter their own, and make it more: and there are some also who gather, yet have less. }25.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Every sincere soul is blessed: but a passionate man is not graceful. }26.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  May he that hoards corn leave it to the nation: but blessing be on the head of
 him that gives it. }27.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that devises good counsels seeks good favor: but as for him that seeks after evil, evil shall overtake him. }28.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that trusts in wealth shall fall; but he that helps righteous men shall rise. }29.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that deals not graciously wit
h his own house shall inherit the wind; and the fool shall be servant to the wise man. }30.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Out of the fruit of righteousness grows a tree of life; but the souls of transgressors are cut off before their time. }31.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  If the righteous scarcely be saved, where s
hall the ungodly and the sinner appear? }1.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that loves instruction loves sense, but he that hates reproofs is a fool. }2.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that has found favor with the Lord is made better; but a transgressor shall be passed over in silence. }3.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A man shall not prosper 
by wickedness; but the roots of the righteous shall not be taken up. }4.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband; but as a worm in wood, so a bad woman destroys her husband. }5.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The thoughts of the righteous are true judgments; but ungodly men devise dece
its. }6.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The words of ungodly men are crafty; but the mouth of the upright shall deliver them. }}
