s cattle; but the bowels of the ungodly are unmerciful. }11.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that tills his own land shall be satisfied with bread; but they that pursue vanities are void of understanding. He that enjoys himself in banquets of wine, shall leave dishonor in his own stron
g holds. }12.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The desires of the ungodly are evil; but the roots of the godly are firmly set. }13.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  For the sin of his lips a sinner falls into snares; but a righteous man escapes from them. He whose looks are gentle shall be pitied, but he that contends in t
he gates will afflict souls. }14.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The soul of a man shall be filled with good from the fruits of his mouth; and the recompense of his lips shall be given to him. }15.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The ways of fools are right in their own eyes; but a wise man hearkens to counsels. }16.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A f
ool declares his wrath the same day; but a prudent man hides his own disgrace. }17.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A righteous man declares the open truth; but an unjust witness is deceitful. }18.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Some wound as they speak, like swords; but the tongues of the wise heal. }19.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  True lips estab
lish testimony; but a hasty witness has an unjust tongue. }20.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  There is deceit in the heart of him that imagines evil; but they that love peace shall rejoice. }21.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  No injustice will please a just man; but the ungodly will be filled with mischief. }22.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Lying l
ips are an abomination to the Lord; but he that deals faithfully is accepted with him. }}
