, even the serpent that flees, upon the dragon, the crooked serpent: he shall destroy the dragon. }2.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  In that day [there shall be] a fair vineyard, [and a] desire to commence [a song] concerning it. }3.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  I am a strong city, a city in a siege: in vain shall I 
water it; for it shall be taken by night, and by day the wall shall fall. }4.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  There is no woman that has not taken hold of it; who will set me to watch stubble in the field? because of this enemy I have set her aside; therefore on this account the Lord has 
done all that he appointed. }5.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  I am burnt up; they that dwell in her shall cry, Let us make peace with him, let us make peace, }6.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  they that are coming are the children of Jacob. Israel shall bud and blossom, and the world shall be filled with his fruit. }7.
{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Shall he himself be thus smitten, even as he smote? and as he slew, shall he be thus slain? }8.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Fighting and reproaching he will dismiss them; didst thou not meditate with a harsh spirit, to slay them with a wrathful spirit? }9.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Therefore shall the iniquity
 of Jacob ye taken away; and this is his blessing, when I shall have taken away his sin; when they shall have broken to pieces all the stones of the altars as fine dust, and their trees shall not remain, and their idols shall be cut off, as a thicket afar 
off. }}
