vineyard. }21.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And he drank of the wine, and was drunk, and was naked in his house. }22.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And Cham the father of Chanaan saw the nakedness of his father, and he went out and told his two brothers without. }23.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And Sem and Japheth having taken a garment, put it
 on both their backs and went backwards, and covered the nakedness of their father; and their face was backward and they saw not the nakedness of their father. }24.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And Noe recovered from the wine, and knew all that his younger son had done to him. }25.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And 
he said, Cursed be the servant Chanaan, a slave shall he be to his brethren. }26.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And he said, Blessed be the Lord God of Sem, and Chanaan shall be his bond-servant. }27.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  May God make room for Japheth, and let him dwell in the habitations of Sem, and let Cha
naan be his servant. }28.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And Noe lived after the flood three hundred and fifty years. }29.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And all the days of Noe were nine hundred and fifty years, and he died. }1.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Now these are the generations of the sons of Noe, Sem, Cham, Japheth; and sons were born to
 them after the flood. }}
