t a good message rejoices him. }26.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A just arbitrator shall be his own friend; but mischief shall pursue sinners; and the way of ungodly men shall lead them astray. }27.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A deceitful man shall catch no game; but a blameless man is a precious possession. }28.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  I
n the ways of righteousness is life; but the ways of those that remember injuries lead to death. }1.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A wise son is obedient to his father: but a disobedient son will be destroyed. }2.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A good man shall eat of the fruits of righteousness: but the lives of tran
sgressors shall perish before their time. }3.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that keeps his own mouth keeps his own life: but he that is hasty with his lips shall bring terror upon himself. }4.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Every slothful man desires, but the hands of the active are diligent. }5.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A righteous man hat
es an unjust word: but an ungodly man is ashamed, and will have no confidence. }7.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  There are some who, having nothing, enrich themselves: and there are some who bring themselves down in the midst of much wealth. }8.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A man's own wealth is the ransom of his li
fe: but the poor endures not threatening. }9.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The righteous always have light: but the light of the ungodly is quenched. Crafty souls go astray in sins: but just men pity, and are merciful. }}
