 to all. }2.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And it came to pass as they moved from the east, they found a plain in the land of Senaar, and they dwelt there. }3.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And a man said to his neighbor, Come, let us make bricks and bake them with fire. And the brick was to them for stone, and their
 mortar was bitumen. }4.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And they said, Come, let us build to ourselves a city and tower, whose top shall be to heaven, and let us make to ourselves a name, before we are scattered abroad upon the face of all the earth. }5.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the Lord came down to see the 
city and the tower, which the sons of men built. }6.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the Lord said, Behold, There is one race, and one lip of all, and they have begun to do this and now nothing shall fail from them of all that they may have undertaken to do. }7.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Come, and having gone d
own let us there confound their tongue, that they may not understand each the voice of his neighbor. }8.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  And the Lord scattered them thence over the face of all the earth, and they left off building the city and the tower. }9.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  On this account its name was ca
lled Confusion, because there the Lord confounded the languages of all the earth, and thence the Lord scattered them upon the face of all the earth. }}
