rtake the righteous. }22.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A good man shall inherit children's children; and the wealth of ungodly men is laid up for the just. }23.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  The righteous shall spend many years in wealth: but the unrighteous shall perish suddenly. }24.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that spares the rod hates hi
s son: but he that loves, carefully chastens him. }25.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A just man eats and satisfies his soul: but the souls of the ungodly are in want. }1.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Wise women build houses: but a foolish one digs hers down with her hands. }2.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  He that walks uprightly fears the Lord; 
but he that is perverse in his ways shall be dishonored. }3.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Out of the mouth of fools comes a rod of pride; but the lips of the wise preserve them. }4.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Where no oxen are, the cribs are clean; but where there is abundant produce, the strength of the ox is ap
parent. }5.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  A faithful witness does not lie; but an unjust witness kindles falsehoods. }6.{\*\cs23\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs32\lang1033\loch\f4\fs32\lang1033  Thou shalt seek wisdom with bad men, and shalt not find it; but discretion is easily available with the prudent. }}
